messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /api/products

All HTTP methods acceptable (override): false

Methods accepted (based on the code, not runtime/implicit behavior):
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- server.js mounts the product router at the prefix /api/products: app.use('/api/products', productRoutes);
- In routes/productRoutes.js, the route for '/' (i.e. the router root) is defined as:
  - router.route('/').get(getProducts).post(protect, admin, createProduct);
  That means the full paths handled by these handlers are /api/products (GET and POST).
- createProduct is attached to POST /api/products in productController.js and is therefore accepted (POST: true).
- getProducts is attached to GET /api/products, so GET: true.
- No explicit handlers for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE, or PATCH are registered on /api/products in the code shown, so those are marked false.
- “All HTTP methods acceptable” is false because there is no catch-all (e.g., router.all or app.use without method) defined for this path in the provided source.
- Note: Some frameworks/servers may implicitly handle HEAD when GET exists, but per your instruction I did not assume implicit/runtime behavior; only explicit handlers in the source code were considered.
